snippet.textDisplay: What are the odds that in the past the rich viewed homeless ppl any different than they do now in any country on earth?  I doubt very much that diogenes existed at all.  He's probably just the product of some writer of the time or a later time meant to convey the idea that wisdom can be found in the most unlikely places.  Probably always the creation of a wealthy writer as well who felt their wealth was much more trouble than it was worth but whom lacked the courage to rid himself of it.  I'm sure in the future they will think many of our characters from movies and books were real ppl.  Probably be statues of Harry Potter and Gandalf some day.
